      <guid>//cloudfeed.net/daily/daily-trust-news-2017-02-05/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Daily Security news from &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/trustpath&#34;&gt;@trustpath&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Credit-card thieves move online as chips cut in-store fraud&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fueling the surge in interest are an increasing number of data breaches at companies that potentially exposed private financial data from millions of &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.tulsaworld.com/washingtonpost/business/credit-card-thieves-move-online-as-chips-cut-in-store/article_f72c28e9-bd12-5420-8113-3c79a2540f1d.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.tulsaworld.com/washingtonpost/business/credit-card-thieves-move-online-as-chips-cut-in-store/article_f72c28e9-bd12-5420-8113-3c79a2540f1d.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;FraudBuzz: Looking ahead by looking back&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data breaches are continuing to contribute to the amount of personally identifiable information or PII that is available on the world wide dark web &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cuinsight.com/fraudbuzz-looking-ahead-looking-back.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.cuinsight.com/fraudbuzz-looking-ahead-looking-back.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Strong passwords are key to data privacy&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NCSA says weak or stolen credentials, including passwords, are a leading cause of online data breaches. Creating stronger passwords is an &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.richmondregister.com/news/strong-passwords-are-key-to-data-privacy/article_7830c476-ea30-11e6-acf0-33e7f860a55d.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.richmondregister.com/news/strong-passwords-are-key-to-data-privacy/article_7830c476-ea30-11e6-acf0-33e7f860a55d.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;5 things to know about new ID scams&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Scammers are hitting consumers with the Can you hear me? scam, tricking them in phone calls to say the word yes and then using that recording to &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.daytondailynews.com/news/local/things-know-about-new-scams/s6stGhBsFWB6Vf6aWfymaJ/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.daytondailynews.com/news/local/things-know-about-new-scams/s6stGhBsFWB6Vf6aWfymaJ/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Police responding to reported armed robbery at Riverside business&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tax scams remain the most common type of scam. In 2016 data breaches at companies and other institutions increased by 40 percent over 2015.  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.whio.com/news/local/police-responding-reported-armed-robbery-riverside-business/4HBh6ysWsWf3FJeJnSW2KM/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.whio.com/news/local/police-responding-reported-armed-robbery-riverside-business/4HBh6ysWsWf3FJeJnSW2KM/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
